 be a hard working, detail oriented and well organized individual. \n\nJulien has helped us in the opening and successful launching of the hotel French restaurant. \nThe restaurant became very fast well known among the international clientele of Wuhan as offering a valuable and consistent product. \n\nIn addition of being a good trainer, Julien is also a good cost controller with the ability to source for local products as much as possible. \n\nFeel free to contact me for further information \n\nPierre-Yves VIOU", "recommendations/0/name": "Julien A. Péchey", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Experience Hotel General Manager from multiple countries and cultures", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/julien-pechey/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAACru3oBorDiYmspXJ_AzS1y0vVjah9kzKk", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "ROMAIN reported directly to Pierre-Yves", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "December 15, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "Pierre-Yves has been a great support to my performances in Novotel Beijing Peace as a big part of my results came from the development of catering through diplomatic market. We have faced very difficult situations sometimes but in each of those occasions he overpassed clients expectations. His main qualities are professional, passionate & incredibly reliable.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "ROMAIN Damien", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "General Manager at Grand Mercure Beijing central", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/romain-damien-56223418/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAOX6RoBda4iwnRVWAG_FocRj8lIhA0j64E", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Peter managed Pierre-Yves directly", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "October 30, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "To Whom It May Concern:\n \nPierre was employed by Novotel Atlantis Shanghai as assistant Food and Beverage Manager from 2001 to 2004. During this period, Pierre has showed a great deal of courage when challenged with different unforeseen situation. \n\nPierre always been rather innovative in many ways and resourceful whenever working closely with his front line subordinates and kitchen team. \n\nYear of 2003, presented extremely difficult period for the hotel business such as SARS and \nNot only that we faced the local cut-throat restaurant business, the biggest challenge was the business travels and the local markets where at their valleys. \nWith a such unwelcome circumstances, never I have a seen a sign of giving up from Pierre.\n \nMoving on, as he always has, Pierre inspired the Food and Beverage team to think creatively and to challenge the odd. Because of his perseverance, Pierre had been very successful at Novotel Atlantis and was promoted to Food & Beverage Manager in Novotel Wuhan \n \nAlthough Pierre had merely worked with me for only  just over a year, I found Pierre \nvery professional, dedicated and very responsible person and will always recommend Pierre for anyone needs expert in F&B operations, with high potential to become RM. \n \n \nPeter Stolley\nGeneral Manager\nGolden Tulip Ashar Suites Downtown Shanghai", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Peter Stolley", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "General Manager at Radisson Blu Kashgar - NOW semi retired.", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/stolley/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJqiUAB7Us4YgDoEP2bjSGld0xrD4Lv3lo", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Julien A. reported directly to Pierre-Yves", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "July 15, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "Pierre-Yves has carried out his duties with drive and enthusiasm and has maintained a high degree of motivation for his team. One of Pierre-Yves strengths has been his ability to coach, guide and encourage his team and develop them to become now strong and permanent manager in China.\nI have worked closely with him and he was a very strong support  for any employee of his department. \nTogether within just 3 months we brought the restaurant \"Le Bistro 98\" to be the best French Restaurant in the city of Wuhan.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Julien A. Péchey", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Experience Hotel General Manager from multiple countries and cultures", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/julien-pechey/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAACru3oBorDiYmspXJ_AzS1y0vVjah9kzKk", "skills/0/title": "Pre-opening", "skills/1/title": "Food & Beverage", "skills/2/title": "Restaurants", "skills/3/title": "Catering", "skills/4/title": "F&B Operations", "skills/5/title": "Hotel Management", "skills/6/title": "Rooms Division", "skills/7/title": "MICROS", "skills/8/title": "Hospitality Management", "skills/9/title": "Hospitality Industry", "skills/10/title": "Resorts", "skills/11/title": "Hotels", "totalExperienceYears": "20.8", "totalRecommendationsGiven": "1", "totalRecommendationsReceived": "3", "urn": "ACoAAAHmXRcB0KHDUhX1HCMfQgYXcZlEZp3K6Uw"}$$::jsonb),
