=JiJATff8z3WPx45i6FJBF-ecku33_hE4nZsAnR4d2oo", "publicIdentifier": "guy-poujoulat-39034a11", "recommendations/0/context": "Guy managed Joanne directly", "recommendations/0/date": "November 29, 2022", "recommendations/0/description": "During my tenure as GM of the Sofitel Bangkok Silom ( now Pullman Bangkok Hotel G ) , Joanne was our DOSM. Albeit relatively small meeting facilities, Joanne helped us put together a good team of Mice and Corporate sales team associates. She was highly organized and managed a wide spectrum of market segmentations among which crews was an essential base business given the high rooms inventory. Back in the days social media platforms weren’t as powerful as now but equipped with a solid brand marketing knowledge Joanne along our PR team helped us positioning well the hotel both locally and internationally. If I recalled correctly back in 2006, the Sofitel Bkk Silom ranked within the top ten hotels in Bkk on TripAdvisor. ", "recommendations/0/name": "Joanne Chung", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Project Director", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/joanne-chung-53861259/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAxe-XwBEkz1hJ29G6ZCg_YJ0tWUfqieE2w", "recommendations/1/context": "Guy managed Areej directly", "recommendations/1/date": "May 31, 2011", "recommendations/1/description": "I've had the pleasure to work with Areej for one year during the pre-opening of the Sofitel Bahrain Thalassa Sea & Spa. Areej managed to quickly adapt to a new envionronment and to a new brand/company. She's  a very autonomous individual and  has always met her pre-opening objectives deadlines. The pre and post opening plans were very well executed as well and Areej showed great commitment in ensuring that all  marketing hotel products and collaterals were up to the brand standards. She's a great asset to the hotel and a real ambassador to our industry. I do miss her vibrant personality and wish Areej all the very best in her present and future endeavours.\nGuy Poujoulat", "recommendations/1/name": "Areej MOHIELDIN , MBA", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "The best MARKETING doesn’t feel like MARKETING!", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/areej-mohieldin-mba-50ab1030/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAaSV9oBBribTnoCt1ZmqgNocOKGmrj1Fd8", "recommendations/2/context": "Guy managed Juergen E. directly", "recommendations/2/date": "April 4, 2011", "recommendations/2/description": "Back in 1996/7 Juergen was the DOE of the Sofitel Raja Orchid Khon Kaen ( newly open), currently a Pullman property .  I was assuming the Resident Manager position and as such Jurgen and I worked very closely. I recollect Juergen as  a very thorough, knowlegeable and trust worthy department head. His current background speaks for itself.\nGuy Poujoulat\nArea GM Sofitel Bahrain Zallaq Thalassa Sea & Spa", "recommendations/2/name": "Juergen E. Seidel (PMI/PMP®)", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Technical Services / Design / Project Management & Pre-Opening Specialist", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/juergeneseidel/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAMDMpcB-uB5yIkrfiCIjtwK-NL1wL-LKpo", "recommendations/3/context": "Guy was Rubel's client", "recommendations/3/date": "June 8, 2009", "recommendations/3/description": "Rubel  was hired as Director of Sales i/c Mice and  Special Projects in Jan 2008 at the Sofitel Wanda Beijing. His primary assignement was to handle the top corporate Olympic service providers (accounts) before and during the Olympics Games. Rubel has exceeded my expectations and both Jet Set Sports, Sportsworld or Aristea just to name a few and their high profile clients staying at the hotel have expressed their outmost satisfaction. \nInSept 08, Rubel was given additional responsabilities acting as ADOSM and he is as of June 09 , the new DOSM of the Sofitel Plaza Saigon. Needless to say that this promotion is the true reflection of his commitment and abilities.\nI wish Rubel all the very best in his new endeavours.\nGuy Poujoulat", "recommendations/3/name": "Rubel Miah", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "General Manager Movenpick BDMS Wellness Hotel Bangkok | Empowering people to drive customer satisfaction, building loyalty and delivering business and financial growth", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rubelmmiah/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAFHtw4BlDMsn44zcX6Ef85SzH4wxLnC_PY", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Clay reported directly to Guy", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "April 8, 2018", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Guy at Sofitel Plaza Hanoi. This was my first position in Asia. Guy played an integral role in developing my hotel knowledge and helping me to adapt to a new culture of leadership in Vietnam. Guy’s knowledge of every aspect of the hotel business is impressive. He is a genuine hotelier that lives and breathes the business.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Clay C.", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "General Manager | Pre-Opening Specialist | Hospitality Entrepreneur | Experienced Luxury Hotelier across 4 countries", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/clayclayton/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAkgvi8Ba814hAiNfIHUdM0vHSbD70Pb8Rw", "skills/0/title": "Hotels & Resorts", "skills/1/title": "Hotel Management", "skills/2/title": "Opening Hotels", "skills/3/title": "Renovation  projects", "skills/4/title": "Pre-opening experience", "skills/5/title": "Food & Beverage", "skills/6/title": "Yield Management", "skills/7/title": "Revenue Analysis", "skills/8/title": "CSR", "totalExperienceYears": "40.3", "totalRecommendationsGiven": "4", "totalRecommendationsReceived": "1", "urn": "ACoAAAJdPZwB17F80k9qkPXfRtrTmcyop-sGwyw"}$$::jsonb);